== Usage

See <tt>aurb --help</tt> for a full list of commands.

= Overview

*--upgrade*:: Searches the AUR for upgrades to local packages that don't exist in any official repository
*--download*:: Downloads your specified package from the AUR and untars it
*--search*:: Searches the AUR for a specified name or description

== Installation

See <tt>ruby setup.rb --help</tt>.

Quick and dirty:

  # ruby setup.rb all

You can install it in ~/bin:

  % ruby setup.rb config --bindir=/home/username/bin && ruby setup.rb install

Or if you prefer RubyGems:

  % gem build aurb.gemspec
  # gem install aurb-0.6.3.gem

There is also a github gem available:

  % gem sources -a http://gems.github.com/ (you only need to do this once)
  # gem install gigamo-aurb

